title: 820-2610-a board not turning on green light
message: I'm guessing 8.4 volts because that's what some of the older boards run on. If you're sure there's no liquid near the SMC or on the board, nothing to worry about then. I'd say see what voltage you get on C7771 when you short the power pads.
